THIS PHOTOSHOOT BROKE ALL MY RECORDS 😱💥🤯

I came back Online and OMG WHAT'S GOING ON? I'VE NEVER SEEN SO MANY LIKES AND SO MANY PEOPLE JOINING MY РАTRЕОN IN ONE DAY AAAAAAA! 😱😳

Tbh I'm still speechless...

I'm really thankful from the bottom of my heart for your amazingly warm welcome for this cosplay 🙏🏻

Thank you! ❤️

I can't wait to send all the rewards for everyone who decided to support me this month on Раtreоn 🙏🏻 (for those who are interested, there are only a few more hours remaining to join) 😉

node.text:
LENORE IS ONE OF THE MOST DIFFICULT CHARACTERS TO COSPLAY FOR ME 🙈

One week past since I showed you the first photo of my Castlevania cosplay and I have to say, that I didn't expect to see SO many sweet comments all over the Internet 😱❤️

I have to admit. Lenore was one of the biggest cosplay challenges I faced... 🙈
I had a brain explosion during my photoshoot 😂🤯
I LITERALLY COULDN'T FIGURE OUT HOW TO BE HER! 

You may be surprised right now.
This costume doesn't seem to be complicated, Lenore is a drawn character with simple traits, I'm a redhead and she is a redhead.
What's the problem?

Her unique strange face and emotions!!! This combination of sexy and dangerous vibe... It's so hard to bring it to life and catch it on photo 🤯

Lenore was a real challenge. And I LOVE CHALLENGES 😏 What do you think about me recreating the end scene with another costume? Yay or nay? Who wants more Lenore from me? 😉

P.S. This photoshoot is available on my Раtrеоn in August 😉❤️ Check it out if you want to see more photos :)

#CastlevaniaNetflix #Castlevania #Netflix #Lenore #cosplay #vampire

node.text:
FAN SERVICE IN COSPLAY? YAY OR NAY? 🤔

Today I reviewed some older photos on my phone and found this cute selfie from my Tifa Lockhart photoshoot.

As you may know, I made a cosplay of her in classic #FF7R outfit, but together with it I wanted to try some photos in dress to help me decide if I want to make her blue ingame dress later 🤔

Of course the black dress from this photo has nothing to do with the game. Tifa never had a dress like that in the game, so it's just my original take.

I had quite a few photoshoots like that: Triss and Ciri in Cyberpunk style, Tifa in evening dress, Sith in black tape ✨

What do you think about cosplays where cosplayers change the outfit of a character, but keep the general attributes and mood? Yay or nay and why? Be honest, I'm interested to know your opinion 🤔❤️

#cosplay #tifalockhart #tifa #games

node.text:
MORE THAN 10 YEARS OF DOING COSPLAY. WHAT'S NEXT?

Today cosplay is a massive part of geek culture and there are hundreds of people in this field who managed to turn their hobby into a full time job and it's amazing!

On the other side, it gives a feeling of... competition? A few years ago in average a cosplayer could create maybe from 3 to 6 costumes per year, but now some people are able to do THAT MANY each month! 

It makes you feel like a loser if you don't match that pace. It makes you feel that you are not as good as the others...

I always wanted to try different things on Instagram, but I did not, because I thought that "people are here just for the cosplay content" and if I do something different THEY WILL ALL LEAVE...

What an idiot I've been 🤣

And do you know what happened? 
A MASSIVE BURNOUT IN 2018. 
To the point that I wanted to quit cosplay. 

What saved me? Simply asking myself "WTF am I doing and for who?" 
Long time ago I started cosplaying as a little 11 y.o. girl and this process was... sacred?
It felt like Christmas every time I did my first ugly makeup attempts, trying to draw anime eyes on my pimply teenage face with very mediocre makeup skills and cheap cosmetics from AliExpress 🤣
But how happy I was! You have no idea! 

All I want is to keep this excitement! To make projects which really mean a lof to me and have fun in the process! Even if I produce not so many cosplays per year. 

In the meantime, please enjoy my non cosplay projects too 😉 This month you can discover me as Showgirl. What an amazing hobby I have! Last month I was a military lady - today a shiny dancer in a plastic costume 🤣 

Thank you for sharing that passion with me ❤️ 

P.S. You know where to find the full photoshoot 😉 (linк in biо)

node.text:
It's time to admit.. I think I'm really into women in uniform 🥺👉🏻👈🏻🧡

Okay, first I cosplayed Olivier Mira Armstrong from #FMA and I loved it, but after Peggy Carter I can say it for sure - a strict looking uniform is my thing! 😂

It's funny, when I was in school I had a lot of problems, because I didn't follow the dress code... (we had strict uniforms in school). Good old times when rebellious Irina tried to enter school in jeans (it was the biggest crime at that time😂)

And now I'm 24 and look at me? I'm eager to wear these uncomfortable jackets and skirts (but just for a photoshoot 😂)

Do you like uniforms on me?
If yes, you know where to find the full photoshoot 😉
Or if you don't know, it's called Раtrе0n and it's the last 48 hours to get this photoshoot together with another pretty project of this month (I will post a teaser tomorrow) 😜❤️ linк in biо

#agentcarter #peggycarter #captainamerica #marvel #cosplay #marvelcosplay #uniform
